{{Infobox German Location |Wappen = Wappen_Chieming.png |lat_deg = 47 |lat_min = 54 |lon_deg = 12 |lon_min = 32 |Lageplan = Chieming in TS.svg |Bundesland = Bavaria |Regierungsbezirk = Oberbayern |Landkreis = Traunstein |Höhe = 537 |Fläche = 37.74 |PLZ = 83339 |Vorwahl = 08664 |Kfz = TS |Gemeindeschlüssel = 09 1 89 114 |Straße = Hauptstraße 20 |Website = [http://www.chieming.de/ www.chieming.de] |Bürgermeister = Benno Graf |Partei = UWG }} '''Chieming''' is a [[Municipalities of Germany|municipality]] in the district of [[Traunstein (district)|Traunstein]] in [[Bavaria]], [[Germany]].
== Etymology ==
The name ''Chieming'', ''[[Chiemsee]]'' and the name of the area ''[[Chiemgau]]'' go back to the Old High German personal name ''Chiemo'' (7./8. century). At the end of the 8th century the name ''Chiemgau'' appeared for the first time in documents as ''Chimigaoe'' but it stood at that time for a smaller area around the village of Chieming.
