:''"Bankim" redirects here. For the [[Bengali people|Bengali]] writer, see [[Bankim Chandra Chattopadhyay]].'' {{Infobox settlement |official_name = Bamkin |image_skyline = |nickname= |image_flag = |image_caption = |image_seal = |image_map = |mapsize = 150px |map_caption = |pushpin_map=Cameroon |coordinates_region = CM |subdivision_type = Country |subdivision_name = [[Cameroon]] |subdivision_type1 = [[Provinces of Cameroon|Province]] |subdivision_name1 = [[Adamawa Province|Adamawa]] |subdivision_type2 = [[Divisions of Cameroon|Division]] |subdivision_name2 = [[Mayo-Banyo]]<ref>[http://www.spm.gov.cm/detail_art.php?iddocument=18&id_art=69&type=doc&lang=en Cameroon Prime Minister's office] accessed 2 January 2007</ref> |subdivision_type3 = [[Sub-divisions of Cameroon|Sub-division]] |subdivision_name3 = Bamkin |leader_title = Mayor |leader_name = |area_magnitude = |area_total = |area_land = |area_water = |population_as_of = 2001 |population_urban = |population_note = not estimated |population_total = |population_metro = |area_metro = |population_density = |timezone = [[West Africa Time|WAT]] |utc_offset = +1 |timezone_DST = |utc_offset_DST = |latd=6|latm=4|lats=58|latNS=N |longd=11|longm=29|longs=24|longEW=E |latitude = |longitude = |website = |footnotes = }}
'''Bankim''', '''M'Bankim''' or '''Bamkin''' is a town and commune of the division [[Mayo-Banyo]] in [[Adamaoua]] in [[Cameroon]]. It is about 9&nbsp;km from [[Bandam]] and 13&nbsp;km from the [[Hoséré Glon]] mountain.{{Citation needed|date=July 2008}} It is one of the traditional [[Tikar]] states.<ref>[http://www.worldstatesmen.org/Cameroon_native.html Cameroon at WorldStatesman.org] accessed 1 January 2008</ref> The area's vegetation is of shrub savanna type.
==History== Bankim is said to have been founded in 1395 by the local chief [[Kimi]] who founded the [[Tikar]] state.<ref>[http://www.almanach.be/search/c/index.htm Almanach.be] accessed 1 January 2007</ref>
==Hazards== [[Loaiasis]] is hyperendemic in this area, but is regarded as a generally mild and painless disease...<ref>[http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/entrez?db=pubmed&uid=11845532&cmd=showdetailview&indexed=google Kamgno J, Boussinesq M, Hyperendemic loaiasis in the Tikar plain, shrub savanna region of Cameroon, 2001] accessed 1 January 2007. Abstract in English</ref> It is reported that about 17% of the population in this area carry HIV/Aids, however the survey is based on urban surveys in the capital.
==Communications==
The provincial road (P26) goes to [[Kakar, Cameroon|Kakar]] via [[Atta, Cameroon|Atta]], [[Sabongari]] and [[Ndop]].<ref>[http://books.google.co.uk/books?id=wrWtrTdBo5MC&pg=PA211&dq=bankim+cameroon&ei=GMZ7R_r1Gp-OtgPsr_n0Cg&sig=Y1H4rIjALOaRbxh8JHy-GehN9vE Planning in Contemporary Africa, Ambe J. Njoh, 2003, Ashgate Publishing] ISBN 0-7546-3346-2</ref>
==Notable residents== * [[Samuel Finlak]], a local photographer who has exhibited in the [[National Portrait Gallery (United Kingdom)|National Portrait Gallery]] in London has retired here.<ref>[http://www.npg.org.uk/live/wocameroon.asp Cameroon exhibition in 2005]</ref>
