{{Infobox person | name = Cassidy Freeman | image = CassidyFreemanComicCon_+_vagueonthehow_2.jpg | imagesize = 250px | caption = Cassidy Freeman at the Comic-Con 2010. | birth_name = | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1982|04|22|mf=yes}} | birth_place = [[Chicago]], [[Illinois]], U.S. | other_names = | occupation = Actress, singer, pianist | years_active = 2006–present | partner = | website = }} '''Cassidy Freeman''' (born April 22, 1982 in [[Chicago]], [[Illinois]]) is an American actress and musician. She is known for her role as [[Tess Mercer]] in [[The CW]]'s [[action (fiction)|action]] [[drama]] ''[[Smallville]]''.
==Biography== ===Early life and education=== Freeman was born in [[Chicago, Illinois]] to prominent Chicago-area attorneys, who also own a cattle ranch in [[Montana]]. She is the youngest of three children with two brothers, [[voice actor]] [[Crispin Freeman]] and [[musician]] Clark Freeman.
Freeman graduated from [[The Latin School of Chicago]] and then [[Magna Cum Laude]] from [[Middlebury College]] in 2005 with [[Academic degree|degrees]] in [[Theater]] and [[Spanish language|Spanish]].
==Career== ===Acting=== Freeman starred in the thriller film ''YellowBrickRoad'' which was written and directed by Andy Mitton and Jesse Holland.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.dreadcentral.com/news/34348/dont-follow-yellowbrickroad|title=DON'T Follow the YellowBrickRoad|publisher=DreadCentral}}</ref> She has appeared in several films and television series. Freeman played the character Veronica Sharpe in the award-winning short film ''[[Razor Sharp]]''. The film won "Best Action Film" at the 2007 Comic-Con International Independent Film Festival. In September 2008, she began starring in the [[Superman]]-inspired science fiction drama ''[[Smallville]]'' where she played [[Tess Mercer]] after the departure of [[Michael Rosenbaum]]'s [[Lex Luthor (Smallville)|Lex Luthor]]. Freeman continued this role until the show ended in May 2011.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.bloody-disgusting.com/news/18354|title=Slamdance '10: First Stills from 'YellowBrickRoad'|publisher=BloodyDisgusting}}</ref> In October 2009, Freeman appeared in the crime drama ''[[CSI: Crime Scene Investigation]]'' episode "[[Coup de Grace (CSI)|Coup de Grâce]]" where she played Officer Donna Grayson, who witnessed her partner arrest, shoot and kill a suspect who turns out to be a fellow off-duty officer. On January 13, 2012, Freeman was confirmed to be in the television series ''[[The Vampire Diaries]]'' as Sage in the third season.<ref>http://www.dreadcentral.com/news/49895/cassidy-freeman-goes-playboy-club-vampire-diaries</ref>
===Music=== Freeman, her brother, Clark Freeman and Andy Mitton formed the band called "The Real D’Coy", where Freeman sings and plays piano.<ref>[http://www.newsarama.com/tv/090501-cassidy-freeman.html 'Lex Schmex' – Meet SMALLVILLE's Tess Mercer] Newsrama.com</ref>
==Personal life== Freeman's hobbies include [[hiking]], [[quilting]], playing [[volleyball]] and [[waterpolo]], [[singing]] and playing [[piano]]. She has a fifty-pound Swiss Mountain dog named Shasta.<ref name=r1>[http://web.archive.org/web/20101215120430/http://cwtv.com/shows/smallville/cast/cassidy-freeman Bios – Cassidy Freeman]. cwtv.com</ref>
===Philanthropy=== Freeman is an active member of the "Heal the Bay" charity, which works toward cleaning up and protecting the West Coast waters and tutors underprivileged children in Santa Monica as a part of the "Virginia Avenue Project".<ref name=r1/>
