'''Moruya''' was an [[New South Wales Legislative Assembly electoral districts|electoral district]] of the [[New South Wales Legislative Assembly|Legislative Assembly]] in the [[Australia]]n state of [[New South Wales]] from 1894 to 1904, named after [[Moruya, New South Wales|Moruya]]. Its only member was [[William Millard (politician)|William Millard]], who held it for the [[Free Trade Party]]. It was replaced by [[Electoral district of Clyde|Clyde]].

