{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2011}} {{Use Australian English|date=July 2011}} {{Infobox Newspaper |name = [[Image:Messenger logo.jpg|200px|News Review Messenger]] |type = Weekly suburban [[newspaper]] |format = [[Tabloid (newspaper format)|Tabloid]] |foundation = 3 July 1968 |owners = [[News Limited]] |headquarters = {{flagicon|AUS}} 23 Wiltshire Street, [[Salisbury]], SA, [[Australia]] |chiefeditor = Matt Deighton |newseditor = Chris Day |staff = John Stokes & Rob Greenwood |sister newspapers = [[Messenger Newspapers]] |website = [http://www.nrmessenger.com.au www.nrmessenger.com.au] | }}
'''''News Review Messenger''''' is a weekly suburban [[newspaper]] in [[Adelaide]], [[South Australia]], part of the [[Messenger Newspapers]] group. The ''News Review's'' area stretches from Pooraka in the south, through to Gawler in the north, and covers Adelaide's northern suburbs.<ref>[http://www.community.newsmedianet.com.au/home/groups/group/title.jsp?titleid=75 News Limited Community Newspapers]</ref>
The newspaper generally reports on events of interest in its distribution area, including the suburbs of [[Elizabeth, South Australia|Elizabeth]], [[Salisbury]], [[Gawler]] and [[Pooraka]]. It also covers the [[City of Playford]], [[City of Salisbury]] and [[Town of Gawler]] councils.
It has a circulation of 89,618 and a readership of 81,000.<ref>[http://www.community.newsmedianet.com.au/home/groups/group/title.jsp?titleid=75 Roy Morgan March 2007]</ref>
==History== [[File:Advertiser Building.JPG|thumb|The office of the ''Messenger'' group of newspapers in Waymouth St, Adelaide]] The ''Salisbury, Elizabeth and Gawler News-Review'', as it was originally known, was first published on 3 July 1968. The creation of the paper reflected the growing population of Adelaide's northern suburbs in the 1960s. In 1977, the paper added Munno Para to its name to become the ''Salisbury, Elizabeth, Gawler and Munno Para News-Review'', In addition to the Wednesday edition, a Friday edition, known as ''The Weekender'', was established on 7 July 1978. ''The Weekender'' ceased production on 16 May 1980.<ref>[http://catalogue.nla.gov.au/Record/2742614 National Library of Australia]</ref> From 6 June 1984 to 13 February 1985, the paper was known as the ''Salisbury, Elizabeth, Gawler Messenger''. The News Review named was revived from 20 February 1985, with the paper renamed the ''News Review Messenger''.<ref>[http://catalogue.nla.gov.au/Record/1508803?lookfor=News%20Review%20Messenger&offset=1&max=10 National Library of Australia]</ref> In 2008, the paper was split in two, with dedicated Salisbury and Elizabeth/Gawler editions.
