'''Karl George Johnston''' (born 26 February 1979 in [[Whitby]], [[North Yorkshire]]) is an English [[Bobsleigh|bobsledder]] who competed for [[Great Britain at the 2006 Winter Olympics]].<ref name=sref>{{cite web|title=Karl Johnston Biography|url=http://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/jo/karl-johnston-1.html|publisher=sports-reference.com|accessdate=7 June 2011}}</ref>
At the [[2006 Winter Olympics]] held in [[Turin]], Italy, Johnston competed in the [[Bobsleigh at the 2006 Winter Olympics – Four-man|men's four-man bobsleigh]] in a team that included his brother [[Lee Johnston]]. The British team finished in 17th position.<ref name=sref/>
