{{HimachalPradesh-geo-stub}}

Four vessels of the [[United Kingdom|British]] [[Royal Navy]] have been named '''HMS ''Plucky''''':

*HMS ''Plucky'' was 212 ton steam tender purchased in 1856 and sold in 1858.
*[[HMS Plucky (1870)]] was a 196-ton iron-screw gunboat that was launched at [[Portsmouth Dockyard]] on 13 July 1870. Renamed [[HMS Banterer|HMS ''Banterer'']] in June 1915. It was sold in 1928.
*[[HMS Plucky (1916)]] was an [[Admiralty M class destroyer|M-class destroyer]] that was launched at [[Scotts Shipbuilding and Engineering Company Limited|Scotts]], [[Greenock]] on 21 April 1916. It was sold for breaking up 9 May 1921, and finally scrapped in 1924.
*[[HMS Plucky (1943)]] was an [[Algerine class minesweeper|''Algerine''-class minesweeper]] that was launched at [[Harland and Wolff]], [[Belfast]] on 29 September 1943. It arrived at Clayton & Davie, [[Dunston]] for breaking up in March 1962.

