{{nihongo|'''Masaaki Kozu'''|神津 正昭|Kōzu Masaaki}} (born November 19, 1974) is a [[Japan]]ese [[cross country skiing|cross-country skier]] who has competed since 1993. His best World Cup finish was ninth in a 4 x 10&nbsp;km relay at [[Switzerland]] in 2001.
Kozu also competed in three [[Winter Olympics]], earning his best finish of 12th in the 4 x 10&nbsp;km relay at [[Salt Lake City]] in [[2002 Winter Olympics|2002]]. His best finish at the [[FIS Nordic World Ski Championships]] was ninth in the 4 x 10&nbsp;km relay at [[Val di Fiemme]] in [[FIS Nordic World Ski Championships 2003|2003]].
